Nov 26 2009 	Very Good Hotel Good Location	Dubai is not the place it once was. Unsure whether the changes I have seen in the last 25 years are progression or disappointment.That aside, Dubai certainly isn't cheap anymore!The Hilton Creek is perhaps 10 years old. The location is good, taxis are relatively cheapThis trip was for leisure. We were checked in about 5 hours ahead of the official check in time and this was appreciated after flying through the night.The hotel has a daily shuttle to the Hilton Jumeirah beach, you need to book in advance and is free. Out at 10am and back at 4pm. This was ideal for us. Our room had a great view of the creek, beautiful bathroom.The hotel has a pool located on it's rooftop. Neither the pool nor the area is that big, but each time we visited, we managed to secure lounges.It offers fantastic views over the creek and city, especially at sunset.I was not impressed with breakfast, since we were room only, had it once and ate elsewhere after.The hotel leaves a copy of Time Out magazine in the bedroom drawer - this is excellent for finding great deals on restuarants.	
Nov 17 2009 	Excellent-we really enjoyed our stay.	We stayed at the Hilton Dubai Creek for 6 nights from the 6th to the 12th of Nov. We paid extra for an executive plus room and it was well worth it. The view from the room was amazing looking out over the city on two sides of the room. The room was big and had a very nice bathroom area with a jacuzzi. We were able to use the executive lounge during the day which had free tea coffee soft drinks and every evening at six complimentary food was served with drinks until eight. Breakfast was either continental in the executive lounge or the full fry downstairs in the restaurant.There was also access to free internet and wi-fi in the lounge.The hotel has a small gym and there is a outdoor pool on the top floor with an outdoor bar and great views of the city. This pool is small.There was one restaurant open while we were there called the Glasshouse. The food was good. Eating out in any hotel restaurant in Dubai can tend to be pricey especially if your having a bottle of wine. Cheapest bottle can often be 30 euro.The hotel also had a free shuttle to the Hilton Jumeriah beach each morning at eleven returning at four. You must book the night before. There is a lovely beach at the other Hilton. From the Hilton Jumeriah there are other free shuttles to the different shopping Malls and they return back to the Emirates Hotel just behind the Hilton Dubai Creek as late as 10pm.The best thing we found about this hotel were the Excellent Staff. They were always friendly and pleasant and could not do enough to help us. They made numerous phone calls for us throughout the week and gave us great advice. The stay we had in the Hilton Dubai Creek was the best and most enjoyable stay we have had in any hotel and we will definitely be returning!Thank you!	
