Oct 22 2009 	Comfortable short stay in Old Dubai	We stayed for two nights at the Hilton Dubai Creek in September 2009, just after Ramadan finished, and the Eid feast after Ramadan was on - the hotel is about a 10 minute drive from the airport and the taxi fare was quite cheap by Australian standards - around $12 from the airport to hotel. The hotel has a lovely rooftop pool with fantastic views over Dubai's skyscrapers. Note that the pool is not covered and as such we tended to have our swim early morning with a cappuccino by the poolside, as it would be too warm in the middle of the day. The hotel is about a 15 minute walk from the new metro stations, however one has to walk through a bit of a dilapitated neighbourhood to get to these and I probably wouldn't recommend that single female travellers walk alone especially at night - we got stared at a lot and I was with my partner. Taxi rides to the Jumeirah beach region are also on the cheap side - I think we paid about $15 - $20 to get to the Madinat Jumeirah entertainment complex. Hilton Dubai Creek is a good choice for people wanting a &quot;stopover&quot; between flights for a night or so, but there really wasn't that much around the hotel so for holidaymakers, I would recommend a Jumeirah based hotel on the beach. We enjoyed our stay at the Hilton, and if we wanted to stay one night in Dubai to break up flight sectors we would gladly stay here again, however if we come for longer I would probably choose a beach hotel. The hotel was spotlessly clean, and I can't fault the hotel amenities or staff.	
