Sep 20 2009 	Excellent Excellent Excellent	MB&amp;SB Oswestry UKJust come back from a one week stay at the Hilton Dubai Creek. What can I say apart from the above. The room had the wow factor as soon as we opened the door and the view we had was fantastic. If you are staying here make sure you get a breathtaking view of the creek. You could see the Burj Dubai, Burj Al Arab and even the QE2 from our room.All the staff are very helpful and courteous and a special mention has to go to Kamal who looked after the pool bar excellently and nothing was to much trouble for him. Cant say one bad word about the staff at all.We loved it when we came back to our room each evening to find fresh towels on our bed but made into the shapes of different creatures. We had an elephant, swans and a butterfly to name just a few. Very original idea.The hotel is close to lots of attractions around the creek but if you are looking for a complete beach holiday then I suggest you look for a resort location on Jumeriah beach. The hotel did run a shuttle bus each morning to the sister Hilton on the beach which was great. It runs at 11am and returns at 4pm.Like other people have said in other reviews Ramadan is not the best time of year to go as you cant eat or drink in public and all cafes and restaurants in all the Malls etc were closed until 7pm. Alcohol couldnt be drank until after 7:30pm and even then you were restricted to wear you could drink. It didnt really affect our holiday as we had the great breakfasts every morning in the Glasshouse which were fab. These kept us going all day so we only had to get an evening meal.Pool is small but is adequate and the views are stunning. Poolside bar for snacks was also very convenient and we ate here a couple of nights and the prices were not to bad. If you want to have an evening meal in one of the two Gordon Ramsey restaurants make sure you have lots of money in your wallet. Verre will write it off and the Glasshouse will severely dent it.Overall a great hotel. Would def recommend staying here but like I said if you want a beach holiday I would look at hotels further down the road.	
