Aug 5 2009 	Brilliant!	We stayed for a two day stopover on our way to Egypt. We decided on this hotel because we wanted to visit the souks, which are close, and we didn't want to stay in crowded and noisy large hotels surrounded by construction work - we were definitely justified in our choice!We booked two executive rooms and the extra cost was definitely worth it with free airport transfers, free breakfast, access to executive lounge all day with free softdrinks or tea/coffee and snacks and free internet access, and a two hour 'happy hour' every evening with free alcohol and very substantial hot snacks (we didn't need to eat dinner either night!).We arrived very early - about 6am - after a long flight and our rooms were ready for us. The staff made us feel very welcome and suggested we freshen up, have some breakfast in the lounge and then take a dip in the rooftop pool - which we did - welcome indeed! Staff everywhere were polite, helpful and friendly - the pool guy brought us glasses filled with ice (unasked) for our bottled water; the exec bar guy made us special cocktails and always filled our glasses up to the brim before happy hour ended; and the cleaning staff were proffessional and thorough, always remembering to replace used items. We felt very pampered.The hotel itself is very classy - all chrome and glass - and the rooms are stunning. Our very spacious corner exec room had two floor to ceiling glass walls with wonderful views over the creek to new Dubai and to the desert in the other direction - did't close the curtains once!. The furnishings were first class and the beautiful marble, chrome and glass bathroom had everything you need and a very nice view from the spa bath.We didn't eat dinner in the restaurants but had a beautiful breakfast in the Glasshouse - a very substantial and tasty buffet.The rooftop pool is fairly small (there weren't many people there so this wasn't a problem for us) but has stunning views and is very clean and well maintained. If you need your fix of sunbathing on the beach you can catch the free shuttle to the sister hotel at Jumeirah Beach - departs at 11am and returns at 4pm each day (about a 30 minute trip). We caught the shuttle there to have a look before our lunch at the Burj al Arab (a great experience!) and, although it looked to be a lovely hotel, we were glad we weren't staying there as the pool and lobby were crowded with people - just not our idea of a relaxing break.The hotel is only 5-10 minutes drive from the airport and a short taxi ride (about $20AUD/10 English pounds) to Dubai Mall and the Burj Dubai. We actually found the taxis quite reasonably priced and used them to take us around to see all the fascinating buildings.I would absolutely recommend this hotel to anyone visiting Dubai (unless you particularly want to be on the beach) and I will definitely stay there again next time I'm travelling that way.	
