Mar 25 2009 	Beautiful room. Surprisingly charming location.	You cannot go wrong staying at this hotel. It was one of the best 4 star hotels we have experienced. If you like &quot;old Dubai&quot; (creekside) as opposed to &quot;new Dubai&quot; (the ultra-luxury areas in Jumeirah about 15 kms. away), this is the place for you. The hotel was designed by Carlos Ott, so the interior is clean and minimalist. Ask for a creek-view room (most rooms are). Definitely try the Gordon Ramsay restaurant (worth the extra price). Your location will overlook the Dhow wharf and will be 3 blocks from the abra crossing to the souk and historic area (catch the abra to the &quot;old souk&quot;). There is a promenade along the creek that affords you a scenic walk (about 6 kilometres return). And, there is a shuttle bus to the Hilton on Jumeirah Beach....definitely leave time for this as the grounds of this beach hotel are remarkable. There is a spa and there are many good restaurants within walking distance (or across the creek by abra...cost is 1 dirham per person). Rooftop swimming pool and bar---small, but charming nevertheless.	
