Sep 5 2008 	Very poor service	I visited the hotel for business In August 2008 and wanted to write a summary of my experience.Good points1. The 'corner' rooms are excellent and have fantastic views over the Creek. These can be booked as the 'plus' rooms. The lower you are however I would assume that the noise would be lounder as you're on a very musy main road. Well worth the extra £20 or so charged.2. The rooftop pool has cold wated pumped into it, and in the really hot months is a great place to relax (well..one of the only places!). The bar is not too expensive (£5 for a cocktail) and the views are great.3. Although small, the gym is very welcoming, has free weights and the changing areas fantastic.4. Verre: although there is little in the way of atmosphere in the restaurant, meat/ fish eaters will like this. For vegetarians, the chioce is poor for the price, and I'd recomment local restaurants (indian/ lebanese).5. Free use of Hilton Jumeriah beach facilities with busses each day directly to the hotel.6. Comtemporary design - if you like glass, chrome and sleek furnishings, this hotel's for you (vs the more 'traditional' Jumeriah beach Hilton).Poor1. The service is appaling. There is a surface of a 'can do' attitude, however beneath this they really don't care. 2. The Executive Lounge is the worst I have ever been to (this offers unlimited snacks throughout the day and free alcohol from 6-8pm. It's free for all Hhonord Diamond members, and you can pay a supplement for access when booking (to an Executive room). The 'food' is rarely replaced and there is absolutely no food after 8pm....not even crisps/ snacks (and it's open until 1130pm!). They're reasonably friendly in the Alcohol hour, but you have to be served (guess to cut down what's drunk!) and after 8pm they put the lights up and only have soft drinks (with the need to always ask for basics like ice etc!!). Utterly poor Lounge, and whilst you may get the financial return if you cram in a lot of drink in the 6-8pm period, this is appaling for entertaining guests/ clients. 3. The management: any problem seems to take ages to be rectified (if at all).....this is in stark contrast to other hotels in Dubai where they really appreciate that clients are paying a lot of money and have options where to go. OverallThis hotel is fine if you like design (and a good Creek view) over substance. If you can overlook poor service, an atrocious Executive Lounge with complett lack of service standards then consider it. The rooftop pool certainly is a big bonus for the location right in Deira. However, should anything go wrong or you expect a touch more personality then go to one of the beach resorts (or a 'city' hotel on Sheikh Zayed road ) where they value custom a lot more. This hotel seems to rely too much on its 'designer name' and Hilton-loyal customers who collect points/ have the company paying.	
