Jun 2 2008 	Sunny Dubai	The hotel was about 20-30 mins from the airport.Me and my family had arrived from the airport about 4 in the morning, but had to wait till about 9 am before we were able to check-in into our room. The room was fairly large and comfortable, and had a good view of the Dubai skyline and the nearby Dubai Creek. However, the breakfast buffet lacked a bit of variety, and is fairly expensive.Dubai, in general, has relatively poor public transport, and traffic was bad from late afternoons till night. We had to move around in taxis, which can be fairly steep due to the bad traffic.The Deira City Centre (the many shopping malls in Dubai) was about a 30 minute walk, if you fancy walking in the sun (mind you, it was 40 C in May! ).An advantage is that, there is a shuttle bus from the hotel, in the morning, to the Hilton Jumeirah Resort, which is about a 40 minute drive away. Along the way, you can view the construction development that is ongoing in Dubai, including the impressive 705m high Burj Dubai (soon-to-be the tallest structure in the world!). Overall, the hotel is generally for business travellers. The hotel staff was, in general, very helpful.For a family vacation, due to its locality, it may cost a bit to move around in a taxi. In addition, one may have difficulty finding food at night.	
