Sep 26 2007	This hotel has it all - ALMOST	I just recently spent a week's stay in Dubai split betwen this property and the Hilton at the beach. As with any stay of more than a day, you discover the good and the bad and this trip was no different.First the good. The hotel is incredibly convenient to walk along the Creek, catch a cab to the Souks, visit the mall, or just gaze over the water all day long. You truly can not beat this location to see what the real Dubai looks like and since its in Deira, there isn't that much construction going on around. I stayed in an executive room on the 11th floor that was very modern and big. There were two easy chairs, a small table, L shaped writing desk and massive bed. The best thing about this room though has to be the bathroom. Huge soaking tub, black marble all over, separate shower - just so nice I could have lived in there. We ate in Gordon Ramsey's restaurant the first night as the drink special on offer at the Glass House packed the place. The food was absolutely incredible but then so was the price (850 AED for 3) with very little wine. The lobby bar is very cool and we had pre dinner or post dinner drinks here every night. I could have lived in here too. The staff are great in true Hilton fashion and the lobby area is stunning.Now the bad. Although offering one of the better views in this part of town, the pool is a big jacuzzi with only about 20 loungers. During Ramadan there are curtains up and you have to eat and drink behind them. It was too crowded on one day to even find a seat and almost too hot the other days. The executive lounge is just as bad - I think there are seats for 18 with the top 3 floors offering executive rooms - you do the math. The last night we were there we sat at the executive check-in desk and had a drink since there were no spots. They do have a computer (that was almost always occupied) that was free for checking email and such but if you wanted to use your own you had to pay the rediculous cost of 100 AED per day or 500 AED for the week. Mind you this is in a room that cost $300 a night. There was maintenance of some sort being done on the right side staircase from the lobby which was very loud during the day to the point that I found it hard to have a meeting.All in all, a great place but if I stay downtown, I'll stay at the Marriott and only come over here for a drink or two.	
