Apr 6 2007 	Fantastic Hotel	Stayed for two nights just before the Easter Bank Holiday Weekend. Got a corner room which was huge. The bathroom was fab with a jacuzzi bath. Both restuarants were excellent (one is Verre by Gordon Ramsey. Beautiful roof top pool on the 14th floor offering spectacular views over Dubai. Excellent Hotel	
Apr 1 2007	Great hotel all-around	Stayed here for two days for leisure, before heading to Fujairah. It is located quite centrally to the Dubai attractions and airport but is a little far from the beaches - the free shuttle will take you to the Hilton beach resort in 20-30 minutes. We really enjoyed our stay in one of the Executive corner rooms, which include executive lounge and airport transfers.The airport transfer left a bit to be desired as the driver wasn't there when we got through customs. Nice car though. We did a very early check-in which wasn't much of a problem. We had to wait about 45 minutes for our room but were invited to use the Executive lounge where we had breakfast. The lounge is quite small but they do serve decent food, unlike most Hilton executive lounges. There's also free wifi internet there.The executive room was very spacious and everything was immaculate. Nice views of the creek through the floor to ceiling windows. Real feel of luxury, especially in the beautiful bathroom with separate shower. Great amenities with fancy coffee maker, printer, plug to charge the laptop while stored in the safe, and Hilton rubber ducky in the bathroom! There's enough space to share with a third person (child or small adult) with a roll away bed.Breakfast in the restaurant was perfect, with everything we could want for breakfast. We were very pleasantly surprised by the variety and quality of each item.Decent pool on the rooftop with loungers. Parking was free, but a little tight to navigate a full size SUV.The only thing I could fault was that staff members at checkin and lounge were very cold - something we noticed throughout the UAE - however they were very professional. Overall this is a very nice Hilton that's a cut above the others in the chain. It should be commended for it's attention to detail and the pervasive sense of quality throughout the property. Recommended if you're here for a stopover or to sample the cultural and shopping attractions.	
