Oct 26 2006 	Fantastic 	My Husband and I are just back from the Hilton Dubai Creek; we stayed there for 2 weeks for our Honeymoon and had a fabulous time. I can’t recommend this hotel enough. Our room was a Creekside view deluxe located on the 4th floor, this was a v large room with a v large bathroom, all freshly decorated and very clean, the view of the creek was out of this world. The only thing to watch out for was the mini bar £2.00 for a can of coke indeed! The amenities in the hotel were ok, the pool is a tad small and there were occasions when you had to wait a short while for a sun lounger, the bar Issimo was nice and the cocktails were good value between £5.00 to £6.00 – the Glasshouse is where you get breakfast, you can choose from pancakes to a full English breakfast and they had plenty of cereals and fresh fruit. It is really well situated and a short taxi ride (5 mins - £2.00) is the city mall here you will find a good selection of shops and eateries. I recommend you take a trip to Karama market as this is where the best deals happen and haggling is expected, we bought so much we had to ditch clothes to get everything in our suitcase! I would also recommend Mina Bazaar as that has also got a varied selection of restaurants and shopsWould definitely advise anyone going to check this hotel out	
