Sep 6 2006	Fantastic	There is not one thing I would change about this hotel. Just in case you are booking for a break here are some things you might need to know;The hotel offers complimentary beach transfers twice daily and use of the Hilton hotel at Jumeriah beach, a good way to get to Wild Wadi, Burj al Arab etc cheaply. It takes about 25mins to get there.The hotel is quite central to everywhere, virtually in the middle of Dubai, you need to get a taxi to most places however we never paid more than about £7 (to the Mall of the Emirates I think)Don't take the trips, desert safari etc from thehotel, you can get exactly the same trips for half the price if you ring the numbers in Time Out etc, which they have free in the rooms!Eat in the Glasshouse restaurant, the food is great, the service is great and the prices are very reasonable.Get your water from the supermarket behind the hotel, for the price of a litre and a half of Hilton's finest you can get about 16ltrs from there!Thats it, the rooms are huge, the bathroom is fantastic, the service is excellent, breakfasts are super and the pool is refreshing!	
