Jul 29 2006 	Great hotel!	My 16 yr old son and I recently returned from a 7 day stay in Dubai. The Hilton Dubai Creek is a great hotel.Although it clearly attracts many business clients it is a welcome break from Dubai's infamous concrete construction sights.The service could not be faulted in the Glasshouse restaurant. Equally, hospitality was extended to us by the porters, housekeeping and front-desk staff. Look out for Benedict, one of the reception staff who is a pleasure to talk to. Nothing is too much trouble. All the staff we encountered would give us tips on things to do and would generally enquire how we were doing whenever they saw us. It wasn't full-on and 'in your face', just sufficiently polite to appreciate their asking. In the morning, they would politely ask what our agenda was for the day and would warn us about over exposure to the fierce heat. I found all the staff to be extremely helpful, accomodating and we were definitely made to feel welcome. Housekeeping is 'on-point'. We woke up to complimentary newspapers and bottled water was delivered every day. In the evening during 'turn-down' staff always lit a candle burner in the bathroom and this created a wonderfully relaxed atmosphere.We stayed in a deluxe room which I think is their standard basic room. It was spacious, modern and extremely well maintained. The decor is tasteful without being too opulent or over the top. The floor to ceiling windows are wonderful with great views of the creek.The bathroom is one of the best I've seen from a 5 star hotel - glass, chrome, black marble. The shower is soothing.Granted, it does not have much to offer families with young children. There is only the roof top pool which is small but never really full, a small gym and spa. I had an hour's aromotherapy massage and slept soundly thereafter. Older children and young couples who want to avoid the hussle and bustle of a typical holiday hotel will appreciate the Hilton Dubai Creek.If you want a crowded beach hotel, lots of water activities and sea, you can always use the Hilton Dubai Creek's shuttle bus to travel to its sister hotel - Hilton Jumeira. Though the service is equally great, the food is not as lovingly prepared. Seemed almost mass produced, and lacked taste. It's easy to jump in a taxi and visit the many malls Dubai has to offer. The staff are most helpful. Always on hand to open doors for you or to hail a taxi. Before leaving for Dubai, I read a review where someone said that the staff at the Hilton Creek were unhelpful. Their comments definitely did not reflect my experiences I would stay at this hotel again without a doubt.The Hilton Dubai Creek allows you to forget that surrounding areas in Dubai tend to be a mass of concrete construction! Even the beach Hilton hotel was surrounded by it. I found this off-putting and was glad that I had made the right choice and decided to stay in the city.	
