Jun 14 2006	What a perfect start	Wiritng this very late as have only recently started adding my experiences to tripadviser but hope it helps.Stayed here on first leg of a three month round the world trip in 03/04. What a great start, this place was unbelievable. The rooms are simply fantastic, all wood, marble, glass, finished to an immaculate standard. Loads of space with all the gadgets you can think of and a bathroom that will make you blush. The floor to ceiling windows give you great views over the creek too.The restaurant is fabulous (Gordon Ramsey I think) and served the most incredible breakfasts which we were delighted to discover were included in our price.The rooftop pool is small but perfectly formed with great views and a nice bar area. Loads of thick white egyptian cotton towels add to the experience.The petal filled pools in reception again add to the ambience and I would disagree with a previous review and say that this hotel is ideally placed if you are a tourist. A short stroll takes you to the wharf where you can enjoy dhow rides down the creek. The souks are a little further on and taxi's are a plenty. We did the big city bus tour (as you see in the UK) and it takes you all over the city. You can get on or off at leisure and see the various malls and things. Would also recommend a visit to the yacht club for the views and over water restaurant there. Also Asha's at Wafi City is a great place to eat.Used the gym which is good too and took the courtesy bus to the sister Beach hotel and boy were we glad we didn't stay there. Nice hotel and beach area but the whole strip is a construction site, or at least it was.Stayed in fourteen hotels on our trip. Three really stood out and this was one of them.	
