Apr 1 2006	Do try Dubai Hilton	Three nights at the Hilton wasn't enough. We could have stayed there forever. The room was large, with a comfortable, Queen sized bed, stylish bathroom and great views of the Creek &amp; the Etislat building. The printer seemed to take pride of place on the desk, which gave the room a rather businesslike feel, rather than one for a holiday. The front desk staff were helpful, polite if somewhat unfriendly. The breakfast room was bright, with a good selection of food on offer. It was a buffet style, so you could have as much as you liked. I throughly recommend the porridge. The hotel's trump card is the rooftop swimming pool. It is not huge, but ideal for a dip, in between sunbathing sessions. It is also a great vantage point for views of Dubai's skyline. The only real downside is that you have to pay to use the Internet. Which is surprising, as it was free at Dubai's Golden Sands apartments. As my laptop is Wi-fi, I managed to pick up a number of signals from the surrounding area.All in all it is a great hotel with fine facilities. Just a shame that it has the feeling of a hotel for business people rather than one for people on holiday.	
