ry effient and the manager evens welcomes you personally. I only saw one child while staying at the hotel. It does have business visitors on a daily basis and they also stay but also a few tourists. Although the hotel was full we never saw loads of people anywhere! It mainly older people that stay here. Not one person below 30 but that suits us women fine as we are very sensible and polite with manners!The rooftop pool is fine.There was always a sun lounger available even though there are only around 40 . Its well enough as most are here on business. The views are breath taking and really set the scene. We sunbathed everyday. The pool man would always offer drinking and move our loungers in the direction of the sun. The bar was at the back area and you can also eat on the rooftop.A shuttle bus runs to the jumeriah hilton 3 times a day but I dont feel theres a need to go there.The service in this hotel is so personal its unbeleivable. They treat you like family and no one is above anyone.The hotel is close to the al karma market where the fake bags are and on the same road as the gold souk. Also the burjuman and diera city mall are very close by. Its very cheap to get around any ways taxi's are dirt cheap.We had cocktails at issimo which I must recommend. I had a mai tai and they do a lovely coktail called ms collins! Dinner at the verre restruant is recommended especially if you are staying here. we chose not to have starters but they bring our bread type sticks with lovely dipping suacing. The service in this place is second to none. They are so attentive and friendly its a joke! For main course I had - caistaing duck brest with five spice turnips, caramelised chestnuts, baby onions and madeira . It was medium rare and ver tastful. The duck brest was exquisite and ive never tasted anything like it. The added extras on the dish made it faultless.My friend had the seabass which she throughly enjoyed.For desert I had the chocolate founde. BVefore that they brouhg out 