Oct 24 2005	Lovely view	We stayed in the Hilton Dubai Creek for four nights towards the end of our Honeymoon. The hotel is very impressive and unbelievably clean. We had a lovely room with a fantastic view of the city. However the bathroom is very dark with all the black marble. We arrived at the hotel at 7 in the morning after an all night flight. Check in is supposed to be in the afternoon sometime but luckily for us we were shown to our room after about 20 minutes.Food was nice but on more than one occasion the service at breakfast left a lot to be desired. Staff very slow to remove dirty dishes and to take orders for hot food. We also tried the room service, food was amazing and arrived very promptly however it took two phonecalls and over 3 hours for them to return to remove the tray.Overall we enjoyed our stay in Hilton but wouldn't recommend it as part of your honeymoon. We had stayed in Legends in Mauritius were you got some nice romantic touches in your room to set the mood for the honeymoon. We had read that Hilton cover your bed in rose petals etc but we have to say there was no romantic touches in our room for the duration of our stay.	
Oct 17 2005	Loved this hotel	We stayed in the hilton for 4 days from the 12th Oct. This hotel is a MUST. The room was lovely with amazing views of the creek, and a wonderful sunken jacuzzi in the bathroom, the bed was huge and the room was very well equipped. Lovely toilteries too! The staff were extremely attentive and couldn't do enough for us. The food was incredble - we dined in both Verre &amp; Glasshouse. Verre was truly delicious and one of the best meals I've ever had - portions were good &amp; the wine list extensive. Glasshouse is less formal but a lovely restaurant serving good food if you want something a little less 'wow' than the Gordon Ramsay Verre.The roof top pool has great views and they serve lovely food as well, although if you don't get there early you may struggle to get a spot! All in all a fab hotel, and one I would return to tomorrow.	
Oct 6 2005 	Great place great rooms but.......	I stayed at the Hilton Dubai Creek Hotel for the biggest exhibtion in the region, GITEX. I know and like the area where it is situated, as you can walk about the dhow wharfage. Although whilst I was there, the road was subject to extensive repair and crossing it was life threatening.The hotel, is without doubt, a high class hotel, for high class clients. The two restuarants offering (standard) high class food (especially Gordan Ramsey's) and the bar very sassy!But, if you want to 'slob' out a bit, watch the big match taking place in Europe-no chance. You can (and I did) walk over to the Sheraton (my prefered hotel in Dubai). Htey have a great variety of restuarants; Indian, Japanese, Italian and the English pub!The roof-top pool is small but adequate, having great views over the creek and city.The rooms are large, clean, well equiped and the bed is very comfortable.Yes I would stay again, but with my wife-not for business. Stay at the Sheraton if you need variation in cuisine.	
Sep 28 2005	This hotel is the business - quite literally!	Having spent four nights at the Hilton Dubai Creek (Sept 12-16) 2005 I can only say that the experience was very very refreshing. Having come from a family wedding in Karachi, Pakistan, my family decided to visit Dubai on the way back to refresh and replenish and also to find out what all the hype was about regarding Dubai having been there 10 years ago when things were much different.We chose to be picked up from the airport at 11pm when our flight landed by the hotel limousine which in this case turned out to be a Toyota people carrier - albeit a very comfortable one. The very courteous driver immediately offered us plastic containers of ice cold mineral water which was a very thoughtful touch as it was 30 degrees at that time of night. Day temperatures reached 49 degrees. The cost of this transportation is 50 dhirams each way which is about 9 pounds, how ever it should be noted that a taxi would probably charge 10 dhirams (around £2.50)On arrival the receptionist could not find a deluxe plus room that we had booked so upgraded us to an executive room which was very very nice. We had panoramic views of the Creek and the business district, this looks amazing both in the day and at night. The bathroom is awesome, our had a sunken jacuzzi bath and a separate large walk in shower. It all done in black marble with lots of mirrors giving a feeling of openess. Next to the jacuzzi was a clay pot with a candle in it which was lit every evening whilst were out and our beds were turned down, this was all part of the turn down service.The Glass House Restaurant and Gordon Ramsay's Vere seemed a bit pricey and I couldn’t see the point as I could always eat in Gordon's London restaurants for the same price so didn’t chose to eat there, but give it a go!Breakfast which was included in our tariff was excellent in the Glass House restaurant, the waiters are very attentive. There is a buffet of cold salamis, breads and so on, in addition you can choose from the hot menu e.g. fried eggs, bacon (surprising for a muslim country - but they cater for all) etc.In all I was very pleased with my choice of hotel in Dubai, I am glad I did not stay by the beach. I visited the Hilton Jumeirah Beach Hotel which seems excellent except for the massive amount of building work that is going on right on top of the hotel with huge skyscrapers being erected as part of the &quot;Jumeirah Residence&quot; development, the cranes being used in this work are massive and plentiful!Hilton Dubai Creek - EXCELLENT !!!!!!	
Sep 22 2005	Great Rooms and Staff a few niggles	I stayed at the Hilton Dubai Creek in September 2005. We had booked a standard room on the 4th floor, but the room was fantastic. The shower was enormous and the bathroom in general was amazing! The staff are extremely friendly and you are made to feel unbelievably welcome. A few niggles; there is a lot of construction work around the hotel and creek which makes it hard to walk around anywhere. Its pretty near impossible to do somethng as simple as cross the road to the creek, not because of the traffic but because there is nowhere to cross it! We did hear noise from the construction work at 3am every morning. There are only 2 lifts in the hotel and we found we spent a lot of time waiting for these to arrive, not helped by the fact that after numerous searches, we couldn't find any stairs, only what appeared to by fire escape stairs! The hotel is also quite dark, both the room and the lobby. The rooftop pool is lovely but can be quite hard to get a sun bed as there are only about 15 of them. I would recommend getting the free bus to the Hilton Jumeirah Beach if you want to do any major sunbathing. Also, I would highly recommend a camel safari in the desert. Great fun!	
Sep 5 2005	Fantastic	My husband and I stayed here for our honeymoon. We had told them it was our honeymoon and they upgraded us to a huge room on the top floor with a balcony overlooking the Dubai Creek. Rose petals had been scattered round the room which was a nice touch. We had dinner on our private balcony overlooking the Creek, very romantic. The room itself was huge and a bath big enough for a rugby team, TV, DVD player and stereo.The glasshouse restaurant was fabulous too, we had a great meal there.Only slight disappointment was the small roof top pool, which was overcrowded and we couldn't get a space around it.But overall, it was brilliant!!	
