Jul 12 2005	Great place to stay on way home from Australia	I stayed in this hotel on the way home to the UK from Australia as part of my honeymoon.We stayed on the executive floor and as a perk of this we got complimentary transport in a chauffuer driven Mercedes to the hotel and back to the airport at the end of our 3 nights. Upon arrival we got taken to the executive floor and checked in the executive lounge. The room did cost a bit extra but was worth the money!!! We had a corner room that had floor to walk windows looking out over the river and towards the beach - although to far to see it!!! We arrived in Dubai at 7am and because the hotel knew we were arriving, they had saved us a room to allow us to check in at such an early time - at no extra cost.The staff were very accommodating and would do anything to help. The pool on the roof is also amazing.Another perk of staying on the executive fllor is the use of the exec lounge all day. During the day you get complimentary sandwiches and cakes and between 6-8pm compliemntary drinks. Basically you help yourself to beers, wines or spirits. Get there early though to make sure you get a seat!!!On our second night when we returned to our room, the house keeper had decorated our room with petals and lit candels around the bath. Very romantic and I got a few bonus points from the wife!!!Would thoroughly recommend this hotel if you didn't want to stay by the beach that is a bit of a constuction site at the moment.	
Jun 3 2005	High Class Hilton	I stayed at the Hilton 3 nights ago for the second time, both occasions with friends on a stag party. The hotel is excellently located to shop, restaurants and night life.I particulary like the rooms, a deluxe plus room is the one to have. I just love contempary style rooms, bathroom dressed in black marble and chrome with a lovely jacuzzi overlooking the creek.Not so sure if it is hotel for families, maybe for couples but definatley for friends/singles, as it is not so romantic as most and is lively on Thursdays with a disco nite.The staff are impecable, my room was cleaned over twice, the bed turned over, candle in the bathroom lit, superb.The swimming pool on the rooftop is excellent, a daily meeting place morning, afternoon and evening.I have stayed in dubai twice and both at Hilton, however when I get married next year maybe look for somewhere a bit more romantic and traditional.Still a top class Hotel!!	
