May 3 2005	Terrible Noise Problems	This visually pleasing hotel markets itself as a contemporary business hotel, but a warning to anyone who requires peace and quiet after a hard day's slog in this frantic city - avoid the Hilton Dubai Creek like the plague. Two stays have been ruined by terrible noise levels emanating from a disco on the mezzanine level. It booms through the bedrooms and sleep is impossible until the music stops around 3am. On the first occasion, a Thursday night, I was told this was a regular party night, the staff were unresponsive to my pleas to end the disturbance and refused to change my room, principally it seems because every room in the hotel is affected. Be warned, the hotel structure cannot smother noise and music from the mezzanine floor. On another stay, this time a Tuesday, the same thing happened to myself and colleagues but was made even worse by a party outside the bedrooms which again went on until 3am. As a result of which our sleep was destroyed and business trips ruined. Fortunately my company has removed this hotel from its approved global hotels list. It is unacceptable that a hotel is allowed to treat its guests in this way and that no amount of discussion with staff or the Duty Manager has any effect. The Hilton Group should be ashamed of this establishment.	
